---
const steps = [
  {
    number: "01",
    title: "Plan before code",
    body: "Every project starts with a document. Not code — a plan. What am I building, what decisions am I making, what don't I know yet. Plan mode forces the thinking before anything is written.",
  },
  {
    number: "02",
    title: "Read the docs first",
    body: "I read the actual documentation before implementing, not after things break. It's slower upfront and faster overall. It also produces decisions I can explain.",
  },
  {
    number: "03",
    title: "Engineer the prompts",
    body: "I write prompts the way I'd write a brief for a contractor: specific about the goal, explicit about constraints, clear about what to avoid. Vague prompts produce vague results — that's a me problem, not an AI problem.",
  },
  {
    number: "04",
    title: "Direct, don't defer",
    body: "The AI does execution. I do direction. When the output misses the brief, I don't adjust to fit it — I correct it and explain why. That's the skill.",
  },
];
---

<section id="process" class="bg-paper border-t border-paper-dark">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">

    <div data-reveal class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-16">
      <p class="font-body text-sm text-ink-muted uppercase tracking-widest">How I work</p>
      <span class="flex-1 border-t border-paper-dark"></span>
    </div>

    <h2 data-reveal class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-light text-ink mb-6" style="line-height: var(--leading-tight);">
      The method is the thing.
    </h2>
    <p data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1" class="font-body text-lg text-ink-muted mb-20" style="max-width: 52ch; line-height: var(--leading-normal);">
      Most people using AI tools don't talk about how. I do — because how is
      what separates building deliberately from building by accident.
    </p>

    <!-- Steps -->
    <div class="space-y-0 mb-20">
      {steps.map((step, i) => (
        <div data-reveal class:list={["flex gap-8 py-10", i < steps.length - 1 ? "border-b border-paper-dark" : ""]}>
          <span class="font-body text-xs text-ink-faint pt-1 shrink-0 w-6">{step.number}</span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-display text-xl font-medium text-ink mb-3">{step.title}</h3>
            <p class="font-body text-base text-ink-muted" style="line-height: var(--leading-loose);">{step.body}</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>

    <!-- Signature: medium = message -->
    <div data-reveal class="bg-paper-mid border border-paper-dark rounded-lg p-8 md:p-10">
      <p class="font-body text-xs text-ink-faint uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">
        A note about this site
      </p>
      <p class="font-display text-2xl font-light text-ink mb-4" style="line-height: var(--leading-snug);">
        This portfolio was built the same way.
      </p>
      <p class="font-body text-base text-ink-muted" style="line-height: var(--leading-loose); max-width: 58ch;">
        Astro was chosen because it ships zero JavaScript by default — right tool for a content site,
        not because it was the familiar one. The design tokens were locked before the first page was written.
        The copy was drafted before the code. The decisions are logged in a decision log.
        I'm not hiding any of that. It's the point.
      </p>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>
